            <scopecontent>
                <p>Personal letters, 1787-1820, of Thomas Truxtun, privateer, merchant ship
                    commander, and naval officer, to Charles Biddle of Philadelphia, a friend and
                    confidant. Truxtun engaged in the China trade, 1787-1793 (6 letters); was a
                    captain in the United States Navy, 1794-1802 (42 letters); and a retired
                    gentleman, 1802-1820 (60 letters).</p>
            </scopecontent>


